parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Extension and Spongy Feel
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pedal extending to the floor or feeling spongy can lead to a loss of braking power, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal extends to the floor
difficulty stopping the vehicle
vibration or shaking of the steering wheel or wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake excessively, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: ABS warning light illuminates
vehicle vibrates or shakes excessively
difficulty stopping the vehicle
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of brake rotors and pads can lead to a loss of braking power, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pads and rotors need to be replaced prematurely
rust or corrosion on brake components
vibration or shaking of the steering wheel or wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to extend to the floor or feel spongy, leading to a loss of braking power and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal extends to the floor
difficulty stopping the vehicle
vibration or shaking of the steering wheel or wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Fuel Filler Neck and Pipe
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the fuel filler neck and pipe can cause fuel to leak during refueling, which can lead to a fire hazard in the presence of an ignition source.
symptoms: Fuel spills onto the ground during or after refueling
fuel filler neck tube is corroded
fuel leaks from the filler neck
fuel filler neck sticks or is difficult to insert
fuel spills back out of the filler neck after refueling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical fire in the steering column can cause a sudden and catastrophic loss of the vehicle, posing a significant risk to occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the steering column
fire in the steering column
gauges shutting down
and "Security" displayed on the dash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of power steering and brakes can cause a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power steering
loss of braking ability
and difficulty steering the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering idler arm can cause difficulty steering, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Clunking noise
difficulty steering
and cracked steering idler arm.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of a wheel from the vehicle can cause a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Wheel disengagement from the vehicle
nut falling off the spindle.
